<font color="#FF0000">AN ISOLATED INCIDENT</font><br>
<tt>Sun Jun  1  3:40:12 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I believe I related the following incident in passing somewhere in the &quot;FORUM&quot;.  When I arrived at LZ English, 173rd Airborne Brigade HQ; the state of the Headquarters Company Mess was rather bad.  The command went through 3 mess sergeants in 2 months.  Many of the cooks spent more time smoking joints than doing their job, and it was hard to just get a decent cup of coffee.                                                                                        <br>
Well, They found a man who turned the situation around in short order.  The cooking improved, and most of the guys got their act together.  However, not everyone was fond of the new regime.  One day someone rigged up a grenade to the sergeant's field phone, and rang him up when he went into his tent.  Fortunately, he went straight to his footlocker and bent over to get something inside.  The blast got his legs and rear.  He was medevacd stateside, but survived.  No one was ever charged with the attempted murder, but half the cooks were transferred shortly thereafter.                                                                              And no, I don't have the details on how the grenade was rigged up.<br>

